{"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/glib\/cond"]}],"sections":[],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Cond","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"metadata":{"symbolKind":"class","modules":[{"name":"GLib"}],"role":"symbol","externalID":"s:4GLib4CondC","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"Cond"}],"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Cond","kind":"identifier"}],"title":"Cond","roleHeading":"Class"},"abstract":[{"text":"The ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Cond","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" struct is an opaque data structure that represents a"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"condition. Threads can block on a "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Cond","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":" if they find a certain","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"condition to be false. If other threads change the state of this"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"condition they signal the ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Cond"},{"text":", and that causes the waiting","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"threads to be woken up.","type":"text"}],"relationshipsSections":[{"kind":"relationships","type":"conformsTo","identifiers":["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/CondProtocol","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/PointerWrapper"],"title":"Conforms To"}],"topicSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Cond\/init(_:)-3cuz9","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Cond\/init(_:)-3wkhq","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Cond\/init(_:)-46zzs","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Cond\/init(_:)-8cx4a","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Cond\/init(_:)-ewbk","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Cond\/init(cPointer:)","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Cond\/init(gconstpointer:)","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Cond\/init(gpointer:)","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Cond\/init(opaquePointer:)","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Cond\/init(raw:)-6h5wo","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Cond\/init(raw:)-91iij","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Cond\/init(retaining:)","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Cond\/init(retainingCPointer:)","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Cond\/init(retainingOpaquePointer:)","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Cond\/init(retainingRaw:)-2zlm8","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Cond\/init(retainingRaw:)-9u70y"],"anchor":"Initializers","title":"Initializers","generated":true},{"title":"Instance Properties","identifiers":["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Cond\/ptr"],"generated":true,"anchor":"Instance-Properties"},{"title":"Default Implementations","identifiers":["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Cond\/CondProtocol-Implementations"],"anchor":"Default-Implementations","generated":true}],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"patch":0,"minor":3},"kind":"symbol","hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib"]]},"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Cond","kind":"identifier"}],"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"content":[{"level":2,"anchor":"overview","text":"Overview","type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Consider the following example of a shared variable.  One or more"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"threads can wait for data to be published to the variable and when","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"another thread publishes the data, it can signal one of the waiting"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"threads to wake up to collect the data."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Here is an example for using GCond to block a thread until a condition","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"is satisfied:","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"(C Language Example):","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"C","code":["  gpointer current_data = NULL;","  GMutex data_mutex;","  GCond data_cond;","","  void","  push_data (gpointer data)","  {","    g_mutex_lock (&data_mutex);","    current_data = data;","    g_cond_signal (&data_cond);","    g_mutex_unlock (&data_mutex);","  }","","  gpointer","  pop_data (void)","  {","    gpointer data;","","    g_mutex_lock (&data_mutex);","    while (!current_data)","      g_cond_wait (&data_cond, &data_mutex);","    data = current_data;","    current_data = NULL;","    g_mutex_unlock (&data_mutex);","","    return data;","  }"]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Whenever a thread calls "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"pop_data()"},{"type":"text","text":" now, it will wait until"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"current_data is non-","type":"text"},{"code":"nil","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", i.e. until some other thread"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"has called "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"push_data()"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The example shows that use of a condition variable must always be","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"paired with a mutex.  Without the use of a mutex, there would be a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"race between the check of ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"current_data"},{"type":"text","text":" by the while loop in"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"pop_data()"},{"text":" and waiting. Specifically, another thread could set","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"current_data"},{"type":"text","text":" after the check, and signal the cond (with nobody"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"waiting on it) before the first thread goes to sleep. "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Cond","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" is"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"specifically useful for its ability to release the mutex and go"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"to sleep atomically.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"It is also important to use the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_cond_wait()"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_cond_wait_until()"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"functions only inside a loop which checks for the condition to be"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"true.  See "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_cond_wait()"},{"type":"text","text":" for an explanation of why the condition may"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"not be true even after it returns."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"If a ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Cond"},{"text":" is allocated in static storage then it can be used","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"without initialisation.  Otherwise, you should call "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_cond_init()"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"on it and "},{"code":"g_cond_clear()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" when done."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"A ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Cond","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" should only be accessed via the g_cond_ functions."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Cond","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" type acts as an owner of an underlying "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GCond"},{"